%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freddits-stock-jumped-after-first-quarter-earnings-report-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHuffman%20told%20investors%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20week%20on%20an%20earnings%20call.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETraffic%20to%20Reddit%20has%20grown%20considerably%20over%20the%20past%20year%2C%20thanks%20in%20part%20to%20users%20Googling%20specifically%20for%20Reddit%20posts%20related%20to%20their%20questions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReddit's%20business%20model%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fipo-experts-finance-legal-strategy-tips-public-market-company-shares-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eseen%20increased%20attention%3C%2Fa%3E%20since%20the%20company%20went%20public%20in%20March%20of%20last%20year.%20Since%20then%2C%20Reddit%20has%20amped%20up%20advertising%20on%20its%20forums%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freddit-openai-deal-ai-data-partnership-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einked%20deals%20with%20both%20OpenAI%20and%20Google%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20allow%20their%20models%20to%20train%20on%20Reddit%20content.%20In%20April%2C%20Reddit's%20stock%20dipped%20after%20some%20analysts%20shared%20fears%20that%20the%20company's%20success%20could%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freddits-success-tied-to-google-search-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einextricably%20tied%20to%20Google%20Search%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BJust%20a%20few%20years%20ago%2C%20adding%20Reddit%20to%20the%20end%20of%20your%20search%20query%20felt%20novel%2C%26quot%3B%20Huffman%20said%20in%20a%20Q3%20earnings%20call%20in%20February.%20%26quot%3BToday%2C%20it's%20a%20common%20way%20for%20people%20to%20find%20trusted%20information%2C%20recommendations%2C%20and%20advice.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20now%2C%20some%20Reddit%20users%20are%20complaining%20that%20the%20uniquely%20human%20communities%20the%20site%20is%20known%20for%20are%20being%20infiltrated%20by%20AI%20bots%2C%20or%20users%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-chatgpt-mistake-big-lesson-explained-only-connect-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erelying%20on%20tools%20like%20ChatGPT%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20write%20their%20posts%2C%20which%20can%20often%20be%20spotted%20by%20the%20formatting.%20ChatGPT%20loves%20a%20bulleted%20list%20and%20an%20em-dash%2C%20and%20these%20days%20tends%20to%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-chatgpt-mistake-big-lesson-explained-only-connect-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeffusive%20in%20its%20positivity%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20user%20in%20the%20community%20r%2Fsingularity%2C%20which%20is%20dedicated%20to%20discussion%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpredictions-for-after-singularity-2015-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadvancements%20of%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20recently%20flagged%20a%20post%20from%20what%20they%20believed%20was%20an%20AI-generated%20user%20spreading%20misinformation%20about%20the%20July%202024%20attempted%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fex-secret-service-agents-how-trump-assassin-could-fire-shots-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eassassination%20of%20President%20Donald%20Trump%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAI%20just%20took%20over%20Reddit's%20front%20page%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20poster%20noted.%20A%20Reddit%20spokesperson%20said%20the%20company%20investigated%20and%20found%20no%20evidence%20that%20the%20user%20was%20AI-generated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20April%2028%2C%20Reddit's%20chief%20legal%20officer%20said%20the%20company%20was%20sending%20%26quot%3Bformal%20legal%20demands%26quot%3B%20to%20researchers%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Zurich%20after%20they%20flooded%20one%20of%20the%20site's%20communities%20with%20AI%20bots%20for%20a%20study.%20Moderators%20of%20the%20forum%20r%2Fchangemyview%20said%20in%20a%20post%20that%20researchers%20conducted%20an%20%26quot%3Bunauthorized%20experiment%26quot%3B%20to%20%26quot%3Bstudy%20how%20AI%20could%20be%20used%20to%20change%20views.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20who%20conducted%20the%20experiment%20said%20in%20a%20Reddit%20post%20that%2021%20of%20the%2034%20accounts%20they%20used%20were%20%26quot%3Bshadow-banned%26quot%3B%20by%20Reddit%2C%20meaning%20the%20content%20they%20posted%20would%20not%20show%20up%20for%20others.%20But%20they%20said%20they%20never%20received%20any%20communication%20from%20Reddit%20regarding%20Terms%20of%20Service%20violations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20moderators%20called%20the%20experiment%20unethical%20and%20said%20that%20AI%20targeted%20some%20users%20in%20the%20forum%20%26quot%3Bin%20personal%20ways%20that%20they%20did%20not%20sign%20up%20for.%26quot%3B%20The%20post%20says%20the%20AI%20went%20to%20extreme%20lengths%20in%20some%20posts%2C%20including%20pretending%20to%20be%20a%20victim%20of%20rape%2C%20posing%20as%20a%20black%20man%20opposed%20to%20Black%20Lives%20Matter%2C%20and%20even%20posing%20as%20a%20person%20who%20received%20substandard%20care%20in%20a%20foreign%20hospital%2C%20among%20other%20claims.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPsychological%20manipulation%20risks%20posed%20by%20LLMs%20is%20an%20extensively%20studied%20topic%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20community's%20moderators%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20not%20necessary%20to%20experiment%20on%20non-consenting%20human%20subjects.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20University%20of%20Zurich%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20school%20is%20aware%20of%20the%20study%20and%20is%20investigating.%20The%20spokesperson%20said%20that%20the%20researchers%20decided%20not%20to%20publish%20the%20findings%20of%20the%20study%20%26quot%3Bon%20their%20own%20accord.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20light%20of%20these%20events%2C%20the%20Ethics%20Committee%20of%20the%20Faculty%20of%20Arts%20and%20Social%20Sciences%20intends%20to%20adopt%20a%20stricter%20review%20process%20in%20the%20future%20and%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20to%20coordinate%20with%20the%20communities%20on%20the%20platforms%20prior%20to%20experimental%20studies%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20spokesperson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Reddit's%20business%20strategy%2C%20which%20is%20largely%20focused%20on%20advertising%20and%20its%20belief%20that%20it%20provides%20some%20of%20the%20best%20research%20around%20because%20it's%20based%20on%20real%20human%20reactions%2C%20the%20increased%20presence%20of%20AI%20on%20the%20platform%20is%20a%20threat.%20And%20Reddit%20has%20noticed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Monday%2C%20Huffman%20said%20in%20a%20Reddit%20post%20that%20the%20company%20would%20start%20using%20third%20parties%20to%20%26quot%3Bkeep%20Reddit%20human.%26quot%3B%20Huffman%20said%20that%20Reddit's%20%26quot%3Bstrength%20is%20its%20people%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20%26quot%3Bunwelcome%20AI%20in%20communities%20is%20a%20serious%20concern.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20haven't%20posted%20in%20a%20while%20%E2%80%94%20and%20let's%20be%20honest%2C%20when%20I%20do%20show%20up%2C%20it%20usually%20means%20something's%20gone%20sideways%20(and%20if%20it's%20not%20gone%20sideways%2C%20it's%20probably%20about%20to)%2C%26quot%3B%20Huffman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20third-party%20services%20will%20now%20ask%20users%20creating%20Reddit%20accounts%20for%20more%20information%2C%20like%20their%20age%2C%20Huffman%20said.%20Specifically%2C%20%26quot%3Bwe%20will%20need%20to%20know%20whether%20you%20are%20a%20human%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20spokesperson%20for%20Reddit%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20Zurich%20experiment%20was%20unethical%20and%20that%20Reddit's%20automated%20tools%20flagged%20most%20of%20the%20associated%20accounts%20before%20the%20experiment%20ended.%20The%20spokesperson%20said%20that%20Reddit%20is%20always%20working%20on%20detection%20features%20and%20has%20already%20further%20refined%20its%20processes%20since%20the%20experimen